plan_fixes:
- version: 1.5.1
  date: '2026-04-17'
  trigger: Cultural overstatement of Ґ, dialogue formatting failures, and beat parsing issues with single
    quotes.
  changes:
  - replace content_outline[0].points[0] — Replace single quotes with guillemets to fix teaching beats
    parsing.
  - replace content_outline[0].points[1] — Remove single quotes around the pedagogical question to fix
    parsing.
  - replace content_outline[1].points[0] — Replace single quotes to fix 'Голосні' beat parsing.
  - replace content_outline[2].points[0] — Replace single quotes to fix 'Приголосні' beat parsing.
  - replace content_outline[2].points[2] — Remove "uniquely Ukrainian" claim for Ґ to address cultural
    accuracy complaint.
  - replace content_outline[4].points[0] — Replace single quotes to fix beat parsing.
  - replace dialogue_situations[1].setting — Force writer to use named speakers instead of em dashes and
    include the required greeting.
  - replace dialogue_situations[1].motivation — Update motivation to explicitly include the reciprocal
    greeting pattern.
- version: 1.6.1
  date: '2026-04-24'
  trigger: Plan check rejected U+0301 combining acute stress marks in 18 place(s). Pipeline adds stress
    marks deterministically AFTER review; plans must be stress-free.
  changes:
  - strip U+0301 from all string values (18 removals)
changelog:
- version: 1.6.0
  date: '2026-04-23'
  changes:
  - 'Review-and-lock pass per the #1412 rubric template (`docs/best-practices/wiki-plan-review-and-lock.md`).
    Paired wiki locked at 9/10.'
  - 'Fixed context-blind reciprocal `А у тебе?` in dialogue_situations[1] (name-exchange context) — replaced
    with `А тебе?` (elliptical for `А тебе як звати?`). Per #1392 Defect 2. `А у тебе?` retained in content_outline[3].points[0]
    for the `Як справи? → Добре. А у тебе?` exchange, where the `у тебе` construction IS contextually
    correct (state exchange, not name exchange).'
  - Added lifecycle markers (lifecycle/reviewed_at/reviewed_by/review_notes) per the convention documented
    in `docs/best-practices/wiki-plan-review-and-lock.md`.
  - Added back-reference to LOCKED wiki (`wiki/pedagogy/a1/sounds-letters-and-hello.md`) in references[].
  - 'Added wiki-plan hooks (closes cross-agent BLOCKER): (a) expanded content_outline[3] with formal greeting
    set (Добрий день / Доброго ранку / Добрий вечір / До побачення / На все добре) matching wiki Крок
    8; (b) added two new activity_hints — fill-in mirroring the 6 rows of wiki "Типові помилки L2" table,
    and quiz on милозвучність + наголос; (c) added grammar items for милозвучність (у/в, і/й) and наголос
    as meaning-maker; (d) extended vocabulary_hints with greeting chunks; (e) extended objectives to cover
    милозвучність/наголос and L2-error prevention.'
  - 'Adversarial scan clean: no Russianisms in plan prose (synthetic `Прочитаймо`, no `Давайте`); no calques
    in vocabulary_hints (all VESUM-verified); no plan-internal contradictions (word_target sum 1200 =
    300+250+250+250+150).'
